    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "The measure — the width of a text column — is among the oldest constraints in type setting. Twelve to fifteen words per line is a longstanding ideal: narrow enough that the eye returns to the left margin without effort, wide enough that each line carries a full thought. This paragraph is held at the standard LETTER margin to demonstrate stable wrap positions and consistent baseline spacing.",
